<div class="l-outer "><div class="js-displayArticleContent spacer-top-35"><section class="section-breaking-news js-editable" data-id="191" data-name="breaking_banner" data-itemtype="channel" data-itemid="162"></section><div class="js-fixedHeader_start article-new"><section id="accessibility-jump-to-content" class="container js-socialShareAdjust"><div class="row"><div class="col-t12"><div></div><div class="meta-container " itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"><h1 class="title article-title" itemprop="name">Pie-in-the-Sky Now</h1><div class="deck spacer-top-20 spacer-bottom-15" itemprop="description">Two scholars argue that Pentecostalism, especially in Brazil, is not so otherworldly as many think.</div>
<div class="article-byline "><span class="author" itemprop="author">By Ed Gitre</span><span class="pipe">|</span><span class="postdate" itemprop="datePublished"><time datetime="2000-11-13">November 13, 2000 </time></span></div>
<div class="article-languages spacer-top-5"></div>
